description: There was a somewhat ambiguous statement regarding Russia attacking Zaitseve from the direction of Kodema
column4: the issue is that there are two Zaitseve. I guessed the one to the south of Kodema might make more sense (11)
column5: although I’m really not sure if this is the correct one. BTW the yellow blotch is a minefield.

description: The Donetsk area: Russia is
column4: for the most part
column5: attacking all of the same areas as they have been for a few days now. The main purpose of these attacks is to surround Avdiivka and force Ukraine to abandon the area the same way they were forced to abandon Lysychansk. Russia has accepted they cannot take the town by fighting it directly.

WKT: Russia is attacking Krasnohorivka (12). A few days ago they jumped across the highway north of Krasnohorivka and settled into the area around the train tracks
name: but since then the news all seems to very explicitly indicate they are attacking Krasnohorivka from the east
description: and not from this position near the train tracks which is to the north. I find this weird.
Russian forces are attacking north towards Avdiivka (13) with little success.

Russians are attacking Pisky (14) and they claim to have simultaneously completely captured the town AND to have failed to capture any additional ground from a few days ago when they claimed to have captured half the town. Logic.
Russian forces are attacking north from Lozove towards Nevelske (15)
column4: this is the only new attack vector

description: Russian forces are trying to capture the farmland around Marinka (16)
column4: which is basically all flat ground that is in direct line of sight of Ukraine’s higher ground. Which seems like a pretty bad place to attack.

description: In the Kherson/Mykolaiv area Russia has added a very large amount of forces
column4: I have heard there are around 28 BTGs. Russia picked the best performing units from all around the war and placed them here to continue an offensive. Where that offensive may lead is a bit up in the air. They could go north towards Kryvyi Rih
column6: today Russia launched an attack on Blahodatne (22). The attack began with a large artillery barrage followed by a ground assault
column7: likely supported by air power. Russia’s goal here is to capture Blahodatne and then go north towards Partyzansk and take the main highway that leads directly to Mykolaiv. However
column8: both Blahodatne and especially Partyzansk are HEAVILY fortified. This attack will be very difficult for Russia.

description: Today
column4: in Nova Kakhovka
column6: a Russian collaborator who was named the “deputy chairman of the administration” was assassinated (23). From the images
column7: it looks like he was gunned down in the doorway/foyer of his home. He was rushed to the hospital (in Crimea???) but died in the car.
